A vintage-style illustration of a tangled, endless red thread winding through an elaborate maze of interconnected gears, springs, and mechanical components, viewed from above. The thread attempts to trace backwards through the impossible labyrinth but splits into dozens of branching paths that loop back on themselves. At the center, instead of a single origin point, the threads dissolve into an ambiguous fog. The color palette features warm sepia tones, aged brass, and deep burgundy, with delicate crosshatching and the aesthetic of an antique technical diagram or Victorian engineering blueprint. Small magnifying glasses scattered throughout the scene peer at different junction points, each revealing yet more complexity beneath.
